<h1 id="sphinxrst">Sphinx/RST</h1>

<p>GNOME <em>Human Interface Guidelines</em> are written in restructured text/Sphinx, however. Escaping to html for images/pictures would be quite cumbersome, but luckily dark mode is supported in the furo theme (and derivates) using the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">only-light</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">only-dark</code> classes. The markup gets a little chatty, but still quite legible. Thereâ€™s some iterations to be made, but in terms of legibility itâ€™s finally a bit more accessible.</p>

